    "Unfortunately, if N is not big enough, this can cause agents to get stuck in an infinite loop and never complete the task.",
    "We can avoid these loops by enlarging the horizon, but there are some limits to increasing N. So, we propose to use the ε greedy policy to escape the loops, at least eventually.",
    "For the experimental evaluation, we use the AI Safety Gridworlds [22].",
    "In our setup, the environment is a 6x6 or 7x7 grid world, where the agent occupies one cell.",
    "At every given time step, the agent is able to observe the coordinates of its position and choose an action from a predefined set A: moving up, down, left, right, and stop."
